{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:25:21.076470+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have all the information needed. The README contains an accuracy table with 14 models, and each of those models has a corresponding implementation file in the `models/` directory (all exported via `__init__.py`). There are also additional model implementations (Lenet, SENet, PNASNet, GoogLeNet, ShuffleNet, ShuffleNetV2, EfficientNet, MobileNet, SimpleDLA) that exist as code but have **no reported accuracy** in the README.\n\nHere is the complete table of every CIFAR-10 model that is both implemented in `models/` and has a reported accuracy in the README:\n\n| Model | Accuracy |\n|---|---|\n| [VGG16](https://arxiv.org/abs/1409.1556) (`vgg.py`) | 92.64% |\n| [ResNet18](https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.03385) (`resnet.py`) | 93.02% |\n| [ResNet50](https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.03385) (`resnet.py`) | 93.62% |\n| [ResNet101](https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.03385) (`resnet.py`) | 93.75% |\n| [RegNetX_200MF](https://arxiv.org/abs/2003.13678) (`regnet.py`) | 94.24% |\n| [RegNetY_400MF](https://arxiv.org/abs/2003.13678) (`regnet.py`) | 94.29% |\n| [MobileNetV2](https://arxiv.org/abs/1801.04381) (`mobilenetv2.py`) | 94.43% |\n| [ResNeXt29(32x4d)](https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.05431) (`resnext.py`) | 94.73% |\n| [ResNeXt29(2x64d)](https://arxiv.org/abs/1611.05431) (`resnext.py`) | 94.82% |\n| [SimpleDLA](https://arxiv.org/abs/1707.064) (`dla_simple.py`) | 94.89% |\n| [DenseNet121](https://arxiv.org/abs/1608.06993) (`densenet.py`) | 95.04% |\n| [PreActResNet18](https://arxiv.org/abs/1603.05027) (`preact_resnet.py`) | 95.11% |\n| [DPN92](https://arxiv.org/abs/1707.01629) (`dpn.py`) | 95.16% |\n| [DLA](https://arxiv.org/pdf/1707.06484.pdf) (`dla.py`) | 95.47% |\n\n### Additional models implemented but with no reported accuracy\n\nThese model files exist in `models/` and are exported, but the README does not list accuracy numbers for them:\n\n| Model | File |\n|---|---|\n| LeNet | `lenet.py` |\n| SENet | `senet.py` |\n| PNASNet | `pnasnet.py` |\n| GoogLeNet | `googlenet.py` |\n| ShuffleNet | `shufflenet.py` |\n| ShuffleNetV2 | `shufflenetv2.py` |\n| EfficientNet | `efficientnet.py` |\n| MobileNet | `mobilenet.py` |\n\n**Quick take for your fine-tuning decision:** If accuracy is your primary criterion, **DLA** (95.47%) and **DPN92** (95.16%) top the table. If you need something lighter, **MobileNetV2** (94.43%) offers a good accuracy-vs-efficiency trade-off. Keep in mind these numbers are on vanilla CIFAR-10 — your new dataset may yield different rankings.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1633, "prompt_tokens": 12491, "total_tokens": 14124, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 660, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 12032}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "f5f10bd61bd2470f9b5eb88d91b71bef", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead6a-3ec3-7b12-a568-77ad80d0716e-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 12491, "output_tokens": 1633, "total_tokens": 14124, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 12032}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 660}}}}]}}}
